event.title: Rohan Shetty Live!
event.disclaimer: Restaurants are solely responsible for the service; availability and quality of the events including all or any cancellations/ modifications/ complaints.
event.description:
Rohan Shetty Trio (RST) wants people to enjoy their music and forget their problems, even if its for a little while. RST plays pop covers and a few originals composed by Rohan. Influenced by the music of the likes of Coldplay, Ed Sheeran & John Mayer, RST believes in simple music which has the feeling of freshness and serenity making the listeners to sing along and dance to their music.

The footprints of RST can be traced back to the days of yesteryears' band, Bugs & Daffy Save the World, Rohan was the lead vocalist and after giving up his cushy corporate job he thought of reviving the band with a new name and set list and there it all started as the Rohan Shetty Trio.

event.title: The Playmores Duo
event.disclaimer: Restaurants are solely responsible for the service; availability and quality of the events including all or any cancellations/ modifications/ complaints.
event.description: Joining the bandwagon of musicians who are contributing to the boom of music scene in the city of Hyderabad is Rinky Sharma, whose first single Zindagi is garnering accolades online and fast becoming popular. When she started out, her inspiration was very different from what it is now. Over the years, she has became more lyrics-oriented, singer, song writer and composer. She adheres to the concept of keeping it simple both the lyrics and melodies which is very much reflected in Zindagi.

event.title: Soulmate Live
event.disclaimer: Restaurants are solely responsible for the service; availability and quality of the events including all or any cancellations/ modifications/ complaints.
event.description: Soulmate is a blues rock band from Shillong, Meghalaya, India. The band is primarily made up of Rudy Wallang (guitar/vocals/songwriter) and Tipriti TIPS Kharbangar (vocals/guitar), although they frequently team up with session musicians (on drums, bass, organ and possibly other backup instruments) when on tour. Tipriti is considered as one of the finest female singers to have emerged from North East India and Wallang is considered one of the most respected blues guitarists of India.
